metadata.name: 𝙲𝙰𝙻𝚈𝙿𝚂𝙾
metadata.description: This hall was flooded one of the first, it had golden walls and a domed ceiling, through which light penetrated and illuminated most of this room, floating into it, we get into the story of its greatness, every centimeter of this hall has its own story. This hall resembled the chambers of the ancient Greek goddess Calypso
